• Saturday, April 2, 2016
  • TSLA

    Tesla Model 3 pre-orders hit 253K

    • Tesla Motors (NASDAQ:TSLA) CEO Elon Musk tweeted that pre orders for the Model 3 hit 253K as of this morning.
    • Musk says he expected orders to be 25-50% of what's actually coming in: "No one at Tesla thought it would be this high before part 2 of the unveil."
    • According to Carnegie Mellon professor Cost Samaras, about 116K plug-in cars were sold in the U.S. in all of 2015.
    • The most basic version of the Model 3 starts at $35K; loaded models will come in at $55K or more.
    • The 200K mark is interesting because the $7,500 federal tax credit is limited to 200K cars per manufacturer under current law.
    • Tesla gained 3.4% on Friday.
